  "text": "Stimuli consisted of 10 Mooney faces, five of which were used in the original Mooney study [CITATION_1] . Mooney faces do not have facial features that can be identified using bottom-up or image-based processes; rather, top-down, holistic processing is required to perceive the image first as a face and only then identify facial features [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
